==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emodin
<hw>Em"o*din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
orange-red crystalline substance, <chform>C15H10O5</chform>, obtained
from the buckthorn, rhubarb, etc., and regarded as a derivative of
anthraquinone; -- so called from a species of rhubarb (<spn>Rheum
emodei</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emollescence</ent>⟦br⟧
